    • add

      String add(int position, T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry at a specified position within this list. Entries are moved one position forward and the list's length is increased by 1.
      Parameters:
      position - is an integer that specifies the desired the position for new entry
      newEntry - is added to the list
      Returns:
      an string indicating if the new entry was added successfully. Handle the error in case the user introduces a wrong entry

    • remove

      T remove(int givenPosition)
      Removes the entry at a given position from this list. Entries are moved a backward and and the list's length is decreased by 1.
      Parameters:
      givenPosition - is an integer that defines the position of the entry to be removed.
      Returns:
      a reference to the removed entry. Handle the error in case of introducing a wrong entry
